Let A = {1, 2, 3} and B = {3, 4, 5}. Find:

1. (A △ B) x {2}
2. A x {2} △ B x {2}
3. (A △ B) x {3}
4. A x {3} △ B x {3}

Show that the answers to questions 1 and 2 are not equal, while the answers to questions 3 and 4 are equal, proving that the symmetric difference of two sets is not associative with respect to Cartesian product.

